description:
Contains a short prose story called "The Gangster, The Whore and the Magician", written by Jamie Delano and illustrated by Tim Bradstreet.

A small mini comic "The First Time" by Brian Azzarello, where we see Young John and a lot of firsts. Such as see a dead body and his "Fag".

Also contains a timeline and character profiles.

Overview

Is it the wrath of an angry god, or all hell breaking loose? In the aftermath of this summer's Will to Power series, Vortex has had it with humanity and decides to leave earth forever! But you can be sure, he's not going quietly! Throw in the final fate of Lt. Eileen Anderson, and it's Vortex vs. everybody -- including the gigantic Hero Zero -- in the stunning conclusion to Out of the Vortex!

Mike Webb is a graduate student from the American Midwest with dreams of re-sculpting the economic face of Eastern Europe. But his capitalist ambitions and his very world come crashing down around him when he learns he has an ancestral connection to a worldwide secret society known as The Unseen Hand. This elite group of movers and shakers has been the true masters of the world for half a millennium, carefully engineering the social and economic destiny of the planet.
name: The Party's Over

description: In an effort to lose his mysterious pursuers, Mike Webb descends into the surreal landscape of the war-torn former Yugoslavia, where he fends off an array of horrifyingly peculiar threats, including a brutal plumber-turned-general and a sexually predatory rock 'n' roll warlord.
name: Ruin, Rape, & Rock 'n' Roll

volume.name: I Was Kidnapped By Lesbian Pirates From Outer Space
I Was Kidnapped By Lesbian Pirates From Outer Space

description: As the KISS 4K try to find out what has happened to their families, they are attacked by the Destroyer Cult's henchman Exciter and his rogues galley (Hard Times, Night Machine, Deuce, Charisma, and Strutter).
name: Legends Never Die

description: As Chikara prepares to infiltrate the Rogues' Gallery to free the captured members of KISS 4K, the Destroyer Cult prepares to bring the house loud down on the Psycho Circus - literally!
name: Legends Never Die
King Kong The Eighth Wonder Of The World
The Tragic Tale of the Fat Female

description: Reprint of 1st issue
name: Scare at the Shore!
Hawaiian music has a sound all its own, but...

description: Collects Ocean (2004) #1-6. Written by Warren Ellis. Art by Chris Sprouse and Karl Story. Cover by Michael Golden. Lying beneath Europa's half-mile-thick mantle of shear ice is the only ocean in the solar system not on Earth. And within those cold waters could rest the key to life on Earth - and quite possibly its extinction!
name: TPB
The Secret Gospel of Maxwell Lord

volume.name: Justice League International: The Secret Gospel of Maxwell Lord

description:
Overview                    

The legendary comic returns with new stories for the '90s! Four all-new adventures and art by Don Lomax, Spain, and Wayne VanSant, with a classic EC reprint from William Gaines' original series, by comics luminary and creator of the original Two-Fisted Tales, Harvey Kurtzman.Two-Fisted Tales, which premiered in 1950, was the first comic series to truly depict the horrors of war. Now this gritty, no-holds-barred comic is back -- with a vengeance! Produced by Byron Preiss Visual Publications for Dark Horse Comics.
name: In Memoriam Harvey Kurtzman 1924-1993
Leo the Lion

deck: Featuring Longshot and Dazzler. Part 1 of 2.
description: Longshot and Dazzler on Mojoworld!
name: Cause and Effect

description:
In a future world ghosts, now called "Blue Light" have been unleashed all over the world. New ways of dealing with them are developed. A detective exorcist named Alice Hotwire stumbles on a case where ghosts don't act as they should and goes behind her superiors to investigate, then things turn to worse.

Created by Warren Ellis and Steve Pugh, this issue has 4 alternate covers all made by named professionals, like Luis Royo, Alan Brooks, and new star Stjepan Sejic.

A green and yellow explosion lights the sky from the top of a residential block as a futuristic police aircraft hovers outside. The pilot maneuvers till he can see movement in the wreckage and radios in to see if agent Hotwire is okay. Hotwire a slight, pale, blonde haired woman in her 20's picks herself out of the wreckage of the stairwell and confirms she's okay. She reports back the situation to the pilot.

A massive ghostly head of a young girl floats above a family in their living room, streaks of electricity connect the face to the father as trails of lightening wrap around his hands and those of his family as they stand in line unable to pull free of each other. The Face claims to be a former family member as it cries out that its lost and unable to find it's way. The measures that usually dissipate such a phantasm have failed and Hotwire's next best idea to flood the area with water is shot down when the fire brigade are tied up elsewhere.

She takes remote control of of the police craft using an internal data connection that allows her to use the crafts controls and systems, seeing the outputs in her minds eye. The craft fires two laser beams that cut into the father legs, dropping him to the floor but fails to sever the connection.

The child's face roars in anger at Hotwire and blows her upwards through the ceiling with a blast of energy. The face demands that Daddy crawls to the edge of the destroyed building facade. The family cry out asking who she is as none of them know who this entity is. In the roof space above Hotwire finds a water tank which she kicks out, making it tumble out over the entity, neutralizing it.

Back at the police station Hotwire gets a quick medical check and we met Peter, a suspended officer with a no nonsense streak.

Alice checks out why a suppression tower failed to effect the apparition she saw and finds its tampered with. Narrowly escaping an attack from the locals she seconds Peter into helping her go back to the bad side of town. They meet Filthy a homeless man with a unique connection with the dead. He taps into the Blue-lights to see if anything is new and is engulfed by a massive skull shaped entity that over charges the local blue-light to the point that other homeless people explode as it chants : Find me, They Want Me, To Do, Bad Things... They Built The Ghost Bomb!
name: Read Me First

description: Appearing for the first time since his revival in THE BOOKS OF MAGIC miniseries, Doctor Occult faces his greatest challenge when his male and female aspects begin to radically interchange. The driving force appears to be his/her repressed sexuality fighting its way to the surface under the influence of Koth, Occult's oldest enemy. Koth's goal is to separate Occult from his female aspect, leading to a desperate quest in which Occult must reconcile his duality - or be obliterated.
name: A Waltz of Screams

object_credits.name: The Mystic Symbol of The Seven

description: After receiving marriage counseling, Dr. Terrence Thirteen is suddenly trapped in a virtual reality. Can he escape before the robots kill him?
name: Do AIs Dream of Robotic Sheep?

description:
Overview                          

Hawkman and The Atom travel to the frozen wastelands of Antarctica! Together they uncover a hidden city built during World War II where a forgotten enemy lurks in the shadows waiting for the chance to break free from its icy prison.
name: Terror Beneath the Ice

description: Can the Hawks survive an attack by the creature known as Darkraven? Hawkgirl thinks so! Plus, Kendra's past catches up with her in a most unfriendly way.
name: The Darkraven

description: It's Hawk vs. Hawk, with New X-Men artist Ethan Van Sciver jumping on board to pencil this special 2-part story! Hawkgirl encounters the person who killed her parents, and she's out for blood! Only one person can stop her: Hawkman!
name: Killers (Part 1)

description: It begins in election year '96 with the country coming apart at the seams. Prez Rickard, long missing and presumed dead, has been sighted at a roadside diner in the American heartland. A trio of restless young misfits, one of whom believes he is Prez's son, sets out across America in search of answers to their country's woes - answers that only the former Chief Executive can provide.
name: Prez: Smells Like Teen President

description: In Massachusetts in 1773 Thomas Hawke gets lost in the woods. He is taken in by the Wampanoag tribe who believe it is their duty to the wolf goddess to 'civilize' him.

Hawkgirl confronts the murderer of her parents - and the Hawks both want him dead!  The question is: Who's going to do the deed?  Plus, tragedy strikes the cast of St. Roch!  Featuring guest-art by Donald Kramer and Prentis Rollins!
name: Killers (Part 2)

description: A fresh look at the Hawks' past begins with Part 1 of the 3-part story arc "The Thanagarian!" Shayera Thal, the space cop from Thanagar once known as Hawkwoman, ventures to St. Roch to discover the truth about her former partner. But Hawkgirl isn't exactly happy to see her…or to learn about the customary Thanagarian greeting! Plus, Hawkman reveals how he copes with loss from life to life. A great place for new readers to jump on board!
name: The Thanagarian (Part 1)

description: In 1975, backed by popular demand, Marvel launched Peter Parker, The Spectacular Spider-Man - an all-new action series starring your friendly neighborhood wall-crawler! In these inaugural issues, never before reprinted in one volume, Spidey faces some of his most fearsome foes - including Tarantula, Kraven, Lightmaster, Vulture, Hitman, Morbius, Brother Power, Hate Monger, Beetle and the Enforcers! Guest-starring the Fantastic Four, Inhumans and Champions! Reprints Peter Parker the Spectacular Spider-Man #1-31.
name: Volume One

description:
Overview                         

The first new Beanworld story in print in over a decade, the Beanworld Holiday Special is the perfect introduction to Larry Marder's inimitable creation!

As enjoyable for children as it is enlightening for adults, Beanworld is a grand adventure that explores social dynamics, culture creation, and ecological networks--all in great fun! Take a tour of this magical world, from Proffy's Fix-It Shop to a Fabulous Look-See Show, in this issue that introduces toys to the baby Cuties and plunges readers into one of the most original and brilliant comic-book universes ever created!

You've never seen anything like it--unless you're a longtime fan of Marder's, in which case you'll be thrilled by the return of this wonderful and peculiar comic-book experience!
name: Holiday Special

description: As the fallout from Doctor Polaris's meddling in the affairs of El Paso fades, a new threat rears its multiple ugly heads. Who is the KDRA and what purpose will Blue Beetle's scarab fulfill? And even more terrifying, will Beetle and friends survive the upcoming Valentine's Day Dance?
name: Only Chance Endures: Part One of Two

description: It's an all-new, rollicking, non-stop adventure tale by Banzai's creator! In a race to save the famed wild asses of the remote Kush mountain range, Buckaroo Banzai and the Hong Kong Cavaliers uncover a large-scale World Crime League operation led by a shadowy figure from the Cavaliers' past. Just who is Dick Ready? Is Tommy ready? Are asses wiped out for their aphrodisiac properties? Who is the mysterious Blind Sheik? Perfect Tommy in an all-out revenge duel to the death - but with knives or guitar solos? A Hong Kong Cavalier breathes his last while another has turned to the dark side? And, most importantly, is any of this caught on tape?
name: Wild Asses Of The Kush

description: How do you save a world that doesn't know it's been taken over? The time for hiding and learning is past! The new master-of-disguise-super-spy Captain Action is forced out into the open to capture or kill all superhumans who have been 'co-opted' by the Red Crawl! One by one, he targets the Public Protectors, the 'people's heroes,' and becomes embroiled in a heated battle with the oh-so-hot Crescent! And they both know she is much better at this than he is! And then, the hunter becomes the hunted - as Captain Action is wanted dead or alive! Plus, an all-new spy thriller tale of the original Captain Action, as well as a brand new jungle action Phantom story!
name: The Enemy Of My Enemy; Gutaale; Many Faces

description: Criminals of Boston, beware! The Masked Gargoyle prowls the rooftops and alleyways protecting its citizens from the villain known as the Fire Devil. By Ron Fortier (Terminator, Green Hornet) and Dario Carrasco (Star Wars). Also: the Fist of Justice battles a robotic menace controlled by his evil arch-enemy, but will he stand victorious?! By Mike Imboden and M.A. Castrillo. Classic comics action and suspense in the Digital Webbing style! IMPH returns in a whacked out short by Steph St. Laurent and Pepijn Berghout. Plus an all-new Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles in full color by Dan Berger and Andie Tong. Gargoyle cover by Dario Carrasco. Justice cover by M.A. Castrillo.
name: Revenge of the Fire Devil

description:
The Vengeance of the Apache Kid!

White man... or Indian? What is the answer to the most puzzling riddle of the West... the mystery of this fabulous warrior whose deeds are still told and retold on the reservations? Here is the exciting drama ripped from the history of the Wild West, a drama of betrayal and revenge in... "The Vengeance of the Apache Kid!"

The Gun That Ruled The West (Text Only Story)

Kid Colt: Judgement Day!

Accused of a crime he didn't commit, a desperate youngster turned outlaw, hunted by day and by night, waiting patiently for judgement day to roll around! And when it did, he found himself fighting side by side with the West's greatest outlaw as their blazing colts thundered in unison for justice!

Blood Will Tell

They tell the story down Durango Way about marshal "Frosty" Bennett, one of the West's great lawmen, and his celebrated gun battle with Wolf Fantell and his mob! The streets of Durango ran red that day that Frosty and his son Billy fought the killer bunch to a standstill! But there's always more to a story than the blast and roar of conflict, and that's what we're going to tell you now... the story behind the story of Durango's most famous gun battle!

Texas Kid: Smoky Showdown!

Texas... sprawling, powerful, a state born in fury and nourished on gunsmoke! Only such an environment could spawn a fighting man like the Texas Kid! Ride with this dual personality avenger in his newest adventure, as he carries holstered justice to an arrogant gang of killer kings, and slams through fire and flame to save his blind father in a... "Smoky Showdown!"
name: The Vengence Of The Apache Kid

description: A flashback details the origin of the hero Afrika, a man who'd rather talk things out then fight...and is talented in both.
name: Afrikaa at Bay

description:
The Fist of Justice returns in an all-new full-color tale blending the best of both worlds, the retro-style heroes of yesteryear in today's times! Created by Mike Imboden and Ed Dukeshire; the Fist of Justice is every comic junkie's dream if you could actually become a superhero in your own mind. Battling the most vicious badguys on the planet and saving the human race! Written by Mike Imboden, penciled by newcomer Chad Hardin, colored by Ryan Scott and lettering effects by Ed Dukeshire.

Also in this issue; the return of Klik-Boom: Exterminators! You didn't think you've seen the last of the blue-jello exterminators, did you? Written and created by Ron Phillips, illustrated by Travis Sengaus, inked by Stacie Ponder and colored by Joel Seguin.

And last but not least -- Academy Award winner for best student animation Rex Steele: Nazi Smasher comes to DWP in an all-new tale written by Matt Peters and Bill Presing. Bill also supplies the art with Antony Mazzotta on colors! Nazi smashing fans shouldn't miss this issue! If you do, we'll tell Rex on you! And you won't want that!
name: Faster Than a...

description:
The Fist of Justice adventure continues! This is it! The mystery surrounding Fist of Justice is answered as the truth is revealed and our hero squares off against the only man that knows his secret. This changes everything!

Created by Mike Imboden and Ed Dukeshire; the Fist of Justice is every comic junkie's dream if you could actually become a superhero in your own mind. Battling the most vicious badguys on the planet and saving the human race! Written by Mike Imboden, penciled by Chad Hardin, colored by Ryan Scott using those funky dot patterns on aged paper effects and lettering by Ed Dukeshire.
name: Able To Leap...

description:
Fist of Justice adventure continues! Since his return, the Fist of Justice can't seem to catch a break. First he discovers he's been out of action for nearly 30 years and has so many questions that need answering. You'd think he'd be able to take a breather here, but nooooo, a giant Atlantian Battle Machine appears in Charm City and it's up to the Fist of Justice to protect its citizens. But what's this? Another one appears? Little does he know, it's actually the Last Paladin.

Written by Mike Imboden and Ian Ascher in their first collaboration. Illustrated by Yildiray Cinar, watch this guy, he's already signed to a series to be published under the Image Comics imprint. Colored by Mick Clausen. Cover by Cinar and Nuckols.

This issue also has a variant cover showcasing the backup feature; Codename: Wicked Angel. Written and created by Ian Ascher, illustrated by Dan Campos and colored by Joel Seguin. Look for the limited edition cover at fitness events throughout 2007.
name: More Powerful Than..

description:
Just when Fist of Justice thinks he can enjoy the beautiful scenic view of Charm City, a giant purple monster shows up. It's an all-out battle issue pitting man against... um, a giant purple monster. Who is this guy? Where'd he come from? All these questions are answered within these pages, Bunky!

Also, for the first time ever, Digital Webbing Presents adds an all-new behind the scenes feature to give you an inside look at how Fist of Justice is created! You'll read commentary from the creators, see unused art, check out thumbnails, rough sketches, and character development stuff. Sound cool or what? Of course it does!

Story and art by Mike Imboden and Dario Carrasco Jr. Colors by Mick Clausen.

Our back-up feature this issue brings back and old favorite for DWP'ers. The Revisionist returns in his last adventure! But is it really his last adventure? We'd tell you, but then you wouldn't be surprised if you pick up the issue, would you?

The Revisionist story by Chad Lambert and illustrated by Ryan Scott.
name: Stranger Visitor...

description: For Fist of Justice, adjusting to life in the 21st century hasn’t been easy. There’s the Internet, smartphones, the War on Terror, Hannah Montana - oh, and a 10-foot-tall monster made of molten rock intent on destroying everything in its path. And what about a rampaging horde of mole men? Suddenly, the 20th century looks a lot better!
name: Charm City Inferno

description: Set in present-day Portland, Oregon PIGTALE relates the exciting adventure of Boston Booth, an amateur private eye whose life is in financial and professional turmoil, when he runs into Clyde, an intelligent talking pig desperate to get away from his violent wolf stepbrother, Taxx. Together, Boston & Clyde venture off into the wild to help one another overcome their fears, rescue loved ones and save the city from Taxx, who's bent on destroying Clyde, getting his revenge and using the super-plasma device to conquer the city and reign supreme!  "PRIVATE EYE: BOSTON BOOTH"  Broke! Unemployed! Madly in love with the girl of his dreams! After being rejected time after time from every private investigation office in Portland, Boston Booth finally gets an interview. Will he get his big break? Will he finally muster the courage to ask Carmen out on a date? Determined to follow in his dad's footsteps and become Portland's best private eye, Boston gives it his all, but his path takes a sharp turn when he runs into a talking pig named Clyde. Come along for the ride of a lifetime! Hang tight and never, EVER eat lard in front of Clyde!
name: Private Eye: Boston Booth

description:
Big Foot, The Loch Ness Monster, The Abominable Snowman, and an alien survivor of The Roswell Incident! Together, these four mysterious legends form "The Enigmas." In this one-shot issue, the secretive squad investigates a paranormal statue in the sunshine state and encounters an unexpected enemy: The Illuminati!"

The Enigmas is an all-ages action-comedy series that teams together four legends. The evil Illuminati have decided humanity has grown boring and wish to replace it with a new species. It's up to these Crypo-all-stars to protect a humanity that doesn't even know they exist!

From Area 51 to Atlantis to other planets, The Enigmas' adventures take them to far reaches of popular myth in their pursuit of The Illuminati.
name: The Enigmas

description: Fist of Justice has an Identity Crisis.
name: Identity Crisis

description: The Firebirds, the mother/daughter super-hero duo introduced in last year's Image one-shot, return to face their toughest threat yet -- the school principle! By the same creative team that brought you last year's original graphic novel from Image Comics; Jay Faerber and Andres Ponce. Also in this issue, another tale of The Mask of the Gargoyle by Ron Fortier (Terminator) and Dario Carrasco (Star Wars), plus the return of The Last Paladin by Ian Ascher and Mahmud Asrar. Cover by Andres Ponce.
name: Firebirds

description: A mysterious orphan on the streets of Rotterdam, no bigger than a bean, will change the world. There’s only one student at Battle School smarter than Ender Wiggin—Bean. Come join X-Men scribe Mike Carey (X-MEN: LEGACY, ULTIMATE FANTASTIC FOUR) and drawn by the amazing Sebastian Fiumara (PICTURE OF DORIAN GREY) for the adaptation of a Sci-fi classic.
name: Part Two

description: In the aftermath of the war, the status quo of Bete Noire has been completely turned over. How will the new Magistrate of Bete Noire cope with this situation? How will the new guardian handle the needs of the city’s helpless? And what exactly does Benny have up his serpentine sleeve?

One way or another, this is the final issue of Galaxy Quest: Global Warning! Jason Nesmith and the rest of the crew of the Protector are all that stand between Earth and its total obliteration by the alien Judgment Ship! Yes, the cast of Galaxy Quest: The Quest Continues. Really. All they need to do is to overcome their innermost insecurities. How many can they have? They're actors, right? Umm... you better order your copies soon!
name: Inherit A Cosmic Wind; My Friend My Self; Once More With Feeling

description: Cowboys and pirates! In the early 1800s, the streets of Galveston, Texas were ruled by crazy French pirate Jean Lefitte and his pal, Jim Bowie! It's true! Google it! And this is their story! It's Deadwood with pirates, man. Pirates! What's not to love?

Where's Glamourpuss? Fortunately most of this issue was 'in the can' before Comics' Greatest Fashion Maven went missing. Cover preview for the proposed glamourtween title, gammagpooz hosts the 3-page fashion horror story, 'The Thinker,' plus a cameo appearance by Cerebus (don't blink or you'll miss him) in his Porsche Carrera 1984 sports car. And Aardvark-Vanaheim continues its 'outreach to the undead' with its second zombie cover, written in the Zombie's own distinctive and emotive language!

It's the return of Captain Valor, his parallel-world alter-ego, Milo, and at least one homicidal ex-girlfriend! DeMatteis' and Abraham's geeeenius super-hero series Hero Squared is back for a three-issue finale that will leave you gobsmacked!
name: The Beginning Of The End!

description: What's the "First Draft,"and what is its awe-inspiring secret? Where did that extra pig come from? What's everybody reading? "The Siege of The Golden Boughs"enters its third installment and the tide begins to turn – but in whose favor? Expect answers, explosions, mayhem and extra tacos.
name: The Book Of Restoration: The Books Of War, Volume Three

description: Leading by example as always, Jonah Hex shows a new town sheriff how to handle both his outlaws and his abolitionists.
name: Cowardice

description: When a major fast food restaurant launches a "Good Taste Need Not Be Alien" advertising campaign, it hires a few aliens for publicity. But who's the marketing genius who thought Null the Living Darkness would make a good employee? And why won't anybody fire him? Battle lines are drawn at a fast food counter when the Fantastic Four stand between hungry citizens and an incredibly powerful, and incredibly belligerent, fast food cashier in, "Would You Like Living Darkness With That?"
name: Would You Like Living Darkness With That?

description: David Balfour and his companion aboard The Covenant, Alan Stewart, have survived the attack of the ship’s crew and now control the ship’s liquor. The reluctant Captain agrees to take Stewart to Linnhe Loch in exchange for bottles of brandy. All seems well until The Covenant strikes a reef and young David is thrown overboard!
name: Part Three

description:
Red Sonja has started on a trek, unaccompanied by her soldiers. She takes a moment’s rest on a broken statue, when her thoughts are suddenly broken by a drop of blood falling on her arm. Sonja draws her sword, and to her astonishment, finds a wounded man of pale skin, tied to a tree above her. The man asks her for help, and if she lowers him from the tree, he will be immensely grateful to her, and reward her handsomely.

Sonja believes them man, and lowers him from the tree. Finding him battered and bruised, she tends to his wounds, and asks him what led to his current state. The man says that he comes from a formerly peaceful village, which of late had been festering human refuse. A priest from other lands came with the promise of returning peace and glory, but instead, he turned his new disciples to something worse. Soon, pirates and robbers were welcomed with open arms. The pale man had tried to cause an uprising, but he had been dealt with, severely, and had been tied to this tree to die.

Hearing his story, Sonja prepares a fire for the man to keep himself warm, and leaves for his village. The man believes that his village has been burned to ashes, but Sonja is not so certain.

Many days later, Sonja arrives at a village, which is currently in a state of deterioration. She walks into a tavern and persuades the keeper to talk. He says that of late, people have been disappearing into the woods mysteriously. Suddenly, their conversation is interrupted by a blonde girl, who wishes to speak to Sonja urgently. She is stopped by the robbers, but Sonja intervenes. A giant of a man tries to knock her down, and the innkeeper shoots an arrow at her. But Sonja skillful as she is, grabs the arrow in mid-air, stabs the giant and the innkeeper, and ends the skirmish.

Sonja and the girl grab two horses and flee the village. They travel through woods, when they are attacked by a pale human. As Sonja deals with him, the girl says that all of this has happened because of a dark priest who came among their midst. She describes that the humans have become “vacant” shells. He had been banished, but has seemingly returned. As the girl starts to describe the priest, she says that he is also a powerful prince, a disciple of the dark God Borat Na-Fori, and has the magic necessary to persuade people. Red Sonja knows that it is the same man whom she freed a few days ago. She promises to set things right, and together, the two women venture into the cursed village.

As they stop on the edge of the village, Sonja tells the girl to stay behind, and scales the city walls. She beholds a sight of destruction and deterioration from above the rooftops. As she takes the aid of a rope to cross between two building, the girl comes up behind her and cuts the rope. Sonja lands on the street, smack in the middle of a crowd of vacant. As she is overpowered, the Dark Prince comes forward, and Sonja immediately recognizes him. The girl proves faithful to him, addresses him as Drelrem, and tearfully asks him to release her mother. But Drelrem stabs her to death. Then he knocks Sonja out.

Sonja wakes up in chains, and finds Drelrem preparing a magic to call forth the spirit of Borat Na-Fori. He tells that Sonja will be a fitting vessel for his Lord Borat. Sonja persuades him to change his mind, but in vain. Drelrem opens a magical portal, and aims a spear at Sonja’s heart. But he misses, and Sonja kicks him into the portal.

As Sonja frees herself, Drelrem rises again, but in a horribly mutated body. Sonja fights him, ad pierces his eye. He accidentally causes a fire, and gets caught in it while Sonja escapes. The vacant chase her. Sonja jumps from the roof of the tower, catches a rope and glides onto the street. The burning Drelrem jumps and lands behind her. As he runs towards her, she puts all her strength in one final blow and decapitates him. Simultaneously, the vacant burn up. Sonja leaves the burning village.

deck: Featuring Longshot and Dazzler. Part 2 of 2.
description: Longshot and Dazzler continue their campaign against Mojo II on Mojoworld!
name: Life Lessons
Sabretooth Unleashed - Second Chances
